== Series ==
The Feminist Press has launched multiple book series.  ''Women Writing Africa'' was begun in 1994 with funding from the Ford and Rockefeller Foundations.<ref name=About_FP /> The four-volume series was completed in 2009.  Like the two-volume ''Women Writing India,'' the series is composed of regionally unique women's literature.  The Femmes Fatales series, featuring pulp, mystery, and noir novels by women writing in the 1930s, '40s, and '50s was launched in 2003, and includes recent releases such as the 2013 ''Return to Lesbos.''

